This paper deals with resource allocation for device-to-device (D2D) communication in 4G networks, which involves aspects of networking, information theory, and system engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the allocation of transmit power and channel, which are related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The proposed energy-efficient scheme involves system-level optimization, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions simulations, which may involve multimedia processing, leading to cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses interference and security issues, which may fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
